{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17616891","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17616891"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:08:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:08:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16443"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16443","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16443"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.77,0.06,0,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9134"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75953"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9134","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9134"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16443"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61454"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1027"},{"type":"tags","id":"3016"},{"type":"tags","id":"4340"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4939"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7567"},{"type":"tags","id":"8663"},{"type":"tags","id":"9616"},{"type":"tags","id":"10152"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21698"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21707"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75953","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75953"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student is assisting in research focusing on early life adversity and its impact on child health and development. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about early life adversity and neurodevelopment is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Early life adversity determines adult cognitive function","Maternal stressors during pregnancy can affect foetal brain development","Genetic factors are more important than environmental influences in neurodevelopment","Psychological stress during pregnancy only affects maternal outcomes","Early life adversity exclusively impacts social and psychological development"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the impact of early life adversity on brain development is crucial. \u003Cstrong\u003EMaternal stressors during pregnancy can affect foetal brain development\u003C/strong\u003E through various biological mechanisms, including elevated cortisol levels and inflammatory markers that can cross the placental barrier and influence foetal neurodevelopment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect statements can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEarly life adversity determines adult cognitive function\u003C/strong\u003E - While early experiences can significantly influence development, the brain remains plastic and outcomes can be modified through protective factors and interventions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenetic factors are more important than environmental influences in neurodevelopment\u003C/strong\u003E - Both genetic and environmental factors play important roles in brain development, with neither being definitively more important\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsychological stress during pregnancy only affects maternal outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E - Maternal stress affects both maternal and foetal outcomes, including foetal brain development and later behavioural outcomes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEarly life adversity exclusively impacts social and psychological development \u003C/strong\u003E- Early life stress affects multiple domains including cognitive, emotional, and physical development\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these concepts is important for healthcare providers to provide appropriate counselling and support to pregnant women, particularly those experiencing high stress levels.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Early life adversity includes stressful events during pregnancy, birth, and early childhood that can affect neurodevelopment.","While early life adversity influences brain development, outcomes are modifiable through protective factors and interventions.","Maternal stress during pregnancy can affect fetal brain development through hormonal and inflammatory pathways."],"references":["Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022).\u00a0The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Van den Bergh BRH, van den Heuvel MI, Lahti M, et al. Prenatal developmental origins of behavior and mental health: The influence of maternal stress in pregnancy. Neurosci Biobehav Rev. 2020;117:26-64. doi:10.1016/j.neubiorev.2017.07.003"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61454"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16443"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61454","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61454"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T15:13:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T15:13:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9134"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75953"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://ap